Detailed Description

The navigation guidance can be retrieved by the method Control::GetNavigationGuidance and gives the information, which navigation keys will be handled by the control. This navigation guidance can be used to e. g. display the available keys between the softkeys as indication for the user.

Member Enumeration Documentation

enum Control::NavigationGuidance::State
 

Describes the state of one navigation key.

Enumerator:
Off  The navigation key is not used and invisible.
Disabled  The navigation key is available but disabled, which usually means that it's shown greyed out.
Enabled  The navigation key is available.

enum Control::NavigationGuidance::Type
 

Describes the available keys for navigation.

Enumerator:
Left  The left arrow key is available for the user.
Right  The right arrow key is available for the user.
Up  The up arrow key is available for the user.
Down  The down arrow key is available for the user.
Center  The center key is available for the user.
